\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Doubt of God\'92s Word:
\f0\b0  "Did God actually say...?" The serpent\'92s first move is to make the Word of God seem restrictive rather than life-giving.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls1\ilvl0
\f6\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Slander of God\'92s Character:
\f0\b0  The serpent suggests God is holding out on them\'97that He is a gatekeeper, not a Giver. Sin begins when we stop believing that God is for our maximum joy.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f6\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 The Desire for Autonomy:
\f0\b0  The core of the Fall is the desire to "be like God." This is the shift from being 
\f6\b image-bearers
\f0\b0  (reflecting His glory) to 
\f6\b image-makers
\f0\b0  (trying to create our own glory).\
