\f6\b\fs36 \cf4 \strokec4 3. The Threefold Fracture (The Effects)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf4 When sin entered, it didn't just break our "legal status" with God; it shattered four foundational relationships. This is a highly transferable concept for new believers:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f6\b \cf4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Relation to God (Shame & Hiding):
\f0\b0  Adam and Eve hid. Instead of running 
\f6\b to
\f0\b0  God, the human heart now naturally runs 
\f6\b away
\f0\b0  from Him. We feel a constant sense of "not being enough" or "nakedness."\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f6\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Relation to Self (Identity Crisis):
\f0\b0  We lose the grounding of who we are as God\'92s beloved. We begin to define ourselves by our performance, our appearance, or the opinions of others.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f6\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Relation to Others (Blame & Conflict):
\f0\b0  Adam blames Eve; Eve blames the serpent. The "Care Covenant" you use in your marriage is a direct response to this specific fracture\'97the tendency to see the other person as the enemy rather than a gift.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\f6\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Relation to Creation (Futile Labor):
\f0\b0  The ground is cursed. Work, which was a gift in Genesis 2, becomes "toil" in Genesis 3. This explains the "restlessness" we feel in our careers and hobbies.\uc0\u8232 
